description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An excellent opportunity to work in a friendly, busy GP Practice. We are currently looking to recruit an enthusiastic, hard working and motivated Medical Receptionist / Patient Advisor to join our dedicated &quot;Front Line Team&quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge of general practice and EMIS clinical system would be desirable but not essential as full training will be provided.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must have excellent communication and customer service skills, basic IT skills and have the ability to work as part of an existing team in a calm and professional manner. The job can be very pressured and is certainly not for the faint hearted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You would be required to work 25 hours a week, Monday to Friday, on a rolling rota consisting of two shift patterns. The first being 7.45am to 1.00pm followed the next day by 2pm to 6.45pm then the next day 7.45am to 1pm again and so it continues.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
